@Kate 

You seem like a person who can define "crunchy" for me in this context.

It's kind of like funky--I both do and do not know what ite means.

@CaptainQuahog I was not upset about abysm but I do think a word being in the dictionary is not a very good benchmark for what is fair or what is "good" fill or not. 

I wish the team would use Google n grams - it measures how often a word appears in usage. I think we could set a lower minimum of frequency and only allow those above it. This would still allow for obscure words but would feel more fair and less random than some that get pulled out. 

Reasonable crossword minds may disagree.
